cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning methods, specifically recurrent neural networks, for anomaly detection in system logs. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of attention mechanisms for model interpretability suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests a potential overlap with neural networks (cs.NE).
